external_knowledge:
- A high hierarchy level indicates a more specific property type within a location, with level 1 being the most general (residential properties);
- Median house price (`medv`) is an indicator of the central tendency of house prices in a given area;
- Average last sold price is an indicator of the market value of properties;
- Ranking by median house price within a location helps identify the relative value of each property compared to others in the same area.

- The specific type of property is determined by property_type_id = 0; 
- The condition of being in good shape is based on the property_condition column; 
- Bounding the Charles River is represented by chas = 1.
